  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 11 October 1928
---
I cannot account for the existence of evil by any rational method. To want
to do so is to be co-equal with God. I am, therefore, humble enough to
recognize evil as such; and I call God long-suffering and patient precisely
because He permits evil in the world.
